    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-28T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.5151/179: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-28T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 28, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. My despatch No. 1063, July 14.<note n="1" xml:id="d628fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> I am informed by the Foreign Office that an agreement has
                    been reached to the effect that 50 percent of the exchange arising from future
                    Ecuadorian exports to France <pb facs="0761" n="673" xml:id="pg_673"/> will be
                    devoted to payment of sums due French nationals. The negotiations have been
                    conducted in Paris and further details concerning arrangement are not yet
                    available here.<note n="2" xml:id="d628fn2">For text of the clearing agreement
                        between Ecuador and France, signed July 27, 1933, see French <hi
                            rend="italic">Journal Officiel</hi>, August 4, 1933, p. 8287.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
